I give that a "C" for effort.

92
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:08,068
Look, I vaguely
know his parents.

93
00:05:08,092 --> 00:05:09,292
They live in my neighborhood.

94
00:05:09,326 --> 00:05:11,776
This is a boy who
needs help, not jail.

95
00:05:11,845 --> 00:05:15,380
- And you're gonna help him?
- I did. I brought him here.

96
00:05:21,504 --> 00:05:23,299
Cheese and grits
from the Silver Skillet.

97
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:25,189
Down, boy.

98
00:05:25,258 --> 00:05:27,170
This deliciousness
is for someone else.

99
00:05:27,194 --> 00:05:29,005
Well, I'm happy
with the lab work

100
00:05:29,029 --> 00:05:30,728
that came back, which means

101
00:05:30,781 --> 00:05:33,615
you are finally cleared for
your bone marrow transplant.

102
00:05:33,701 --> 00:05:35,127
We can start your
conditioning today.

103
00:05:35,151 --> 00:05:36,718
Dr. Pravesh?

104
00:05:36,787 --> 00:05:39,938
Yeah, so first you'll
receive a series

105
00:05:40,007 --> 00:05:42,107
of Bu-Flu chemo blasts to ensure

106
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:44,136
that all the bone
marrow is cleared out.

107
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:46,127
And then we can
perform an allogeneic

108
00:05:46,213 --> 00:05:48,680
hematopoietic
stem cell transplant.

109
00:05:48,749 --> 00:05:51,216
Wow. You know, when
you break it down like that,

110
00:05:51,284 --> 00:05:53,201
it seems so simple.

111
00:05:53,270 --> 00:05:56,537
Why don't you try that again,
but this time not in Latin.

112
00:05:56,606 --> 00:05:58,240
Okay. Sorry.

113
00:05:58,308 --> 00:06:01,108
So, basically, we're going
to take donor stem cells

114
00:06:01,177 --> 00:06:03,445
and have them set up
shop in your bone marrow

115
00:06:03,513 --> 00:06:04,980
and populate your immune system.

116
00:06:05,065 --> 00:06:06,297
Right. Once that's done,

117
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:08,286
your new and improved
immune system

118
00:06:08,335 --> 00:06:11,135
will recognize any
remaining leukemia cells

119
00:06:11,205 --> 00:06:13,104
as foreign, and attack them.

120
00:06:16,392 --> 00:06:18,092
Go ahead and take that.

121
00:06:18,162 --> 00:06:20,328
I can finish up in here.

122
00:06:21,531 --> 00:06:23,331
Hey. Why'd you page me?

123
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:25,950
Hey. I need you to keep
an eye on Lily for me.

124
00:06:26,019 --> 00:06:27,519
I was taken off her team.

125
00:06:27,588 --> 00:06:29,849
Yeah, I heard about that,
Nic. Wait-wait-wait-wait.

126
00:06:29,873 --> 00:06:31,122
What's going on?

127
00:06:33,127 --> 00:06:35,776
All right, come on.

128
00:06:40,184 --> 00:06:41,184
Close the door.

129
00:06:42,385 --> 00:06:43,968
Is all this really necessary?

130
00:06:44,021 --> 00:06:46,388
I think Lane's committing
insurance fraud

131
00:06:46,456 --> 00:06:49,924
