They say the way to a woman's
heart is through her stomach.

197
00:09:46,202 --> 00:09:48,397
Actually, I think that's the way
to a man's heart, but thanks,

198
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:51,539
- Irving loved them.
- You gave away my gift?

199
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:53,268
Mm, "gift" is a strong
word. This is more like

200
00:09:53,292 --> 00:09:55,605
you passed a bush, saw a flower
sticking out, plucked it for me,

201
00:09:55,629 --> 00:09:57,390
and then said, "Hey,
look... I bought you flowers."

202
00:09:57,414 --> 00:10:01,215
- Wow. Tough crowd. Okay.
- Have you seen Mina?

203
00:10:01,284 --> 00:10:03,496
I heard she took on a
gang of muggers last night.

204
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:05,248
It's all anyone's
talking about upstairs.

205
00:10:05,272 --> 00:10:08,406
- I - need some
help in here! Now!

206
00:10:08,475 --> 00:10:12,193
- Damn it, Atiba, calm down!
- Easy, buddy, easy!

207
00:10:12,262 --> 00:10:13,456
He's going through withdrawal.

208
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,395
He tried to take
a chunk out of me!

209
00:10:14,464 --> 00:10:15,584
Give me two of lorazepam.

210
00:10:15,631 --> 00:10:17,599
Code Gray! Bed three!

211
00:10:17,667 --> 00:10:19,547
Okay.

212
00:10:21,354 --> 00:10:23,571
Okay.

213
00:10:31,481 --> 00:10:33,064
How's Atiba?

214
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:34,632
Calmer. Drowsy. Restrained.

215
00:10:34,701 --> 00:10:37,485
- You need to call his parents.
- Me? Why me?

216
00:10:37,554 --> 00:10:40,422
Because someone needs to tell
them to come pick up their son.

217
00:10:40,507 --> 00:10:42,507
I don't do people.

218
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:46,277
I thought you were
still on vacation.

219
00:10:47,681 --> 00:10:49,213
My sister-in-law's in town.

220
00:10:49,282 --> 00:10:50,882
Not a fan?

221
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:52,984
- Want to grab a coffee?
- Sure.

222
00:10:53,053 --> 00:10:55,953
- Be happy you don't have in-laws anymore.
- Oh, I am.

223
00:10:56,022 --> 00:10:58,422
By the way, that
golf buddy of mine,

224
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:02,126
- the one with the tremor...
- Right. How's he doing?

225
00:11:02,195 --> 00:11:03,939
Well, he's had to
lay off the benzos.

226
00:11:03,963 --> 00:11:05,691
The side effects were
too aggressive for him.

227
00:11:05,715 --> 00:11:08,616
And now he's all wound up
about the tremor returning, and...

228
00:11:08,685 --> 00:11:11,635
Well, he's right
to be concerned.

229
00:11:11,705 --> 00:11:13,149
If the tremor is
really interfering

230
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:14,389
with his quality of life,

231
00:11:14,458 --> 00:11:15,468
your friend may ultimately

232
00:11:15,492 --> 00:11:16,424
have to consider brain surgery.

233
00:11:16,493 --> 00:11:17,759
And we both know

234
00:11:17,827 --> 00:11:18,837
when the air hits your brain...

235
00:11:18,861 --> 00:11:20,495
You're never the same.

236
00:11:23,533 --> 00:11:25,433
<i>No, this is...</i>

237
00:11:25,501 --> 00:11:27,468
this is a hospital, Mr. Jackson,

238
00:11:27,536 --> 00:11:29,554
not a hotel. No.

239
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:31,672
No, we don't have
courtesy shuttles.

240
00:11:31,741 --> 00:11:35,076
Well, you'll just have
to come get Atiba.

241
00:11:35,145 --> 00:11:36,627
Hello?

242
00:11:37,698 --> 00:11:38,630
Hello?

243
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:40,915
Are you kidding me?

244
00:11:40,984 --> 00:11:42,366
You okay?

245
00:11:42,435 --> 00:11:44,315
Nothing a little caffeine

246
00:11:44,354 --> 00:11:46,503
- can't fix.
- Oh.

247
00:11:48,208 --> 00:11:49,941
Mmm. It's been a long shift

248
00:11:50,010 --> 00:11:51,925
that is thankfully almost over.

249
00:11:51,994 --> 00:11:53,127
Well, maybe this

