- it had fallen off.
- Lara found it on the floor

253
00:11:58,335 --> 00:11:59,500
of the nurses' lounge.

254
00:11:59,569 --> 00:12:02,303
I'm simply doing the
honor of returning it.

255
00:12:04,391 --> 00:12:05,590
There you go.

256
00:12:05,658 --> 00:12:07,157
I see you wear it all the time.

257
00:12:07,226 --> 00:12:08,687
Figured it's one
of your favorites.

258
00:12:08,711 --> 00:12:10,694
Well, thank you. I owe you one.

259
00:12:10,764 --> 00:12:12,112
Really?

260
00:12:12,182 --> 00:12:13,182
Get over yourself.

261
00:12:13,216 --> 00:12:15,617
I'll see you later.

262
00:12:15,685 --> 00:12:16,967
Hey, Conrad!

263
00:12:17,036 --> 00:12:19,153
Whatever it is, figure it out.

264
00:12:19,239 --> 00:12:20,071
No can do.

265
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,639
I need reinforcements.

266
00:12:29,282 --> 00:12:31,511
The priority is to get to
the source of your pain,

267
00:12:31,535 --> 00:12:33,429
be it psychological,
neurological...

268
00:12:33,453 --> 00:12:35,736
- This is not in my head.
- This is a GI problem.

269
00:12:35,805 --> 00:12:37,216
We'll need to do
a battery of tests,

270
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:39,218
starting with a colonoscopy
and upper endoscopy...

271
00:12:39,242 --> 00:12:41,387
That's fine, but after I get
nerve condition studies.

272
00:12:41,411 --> 00:12:43,744
- This is neuropathic.
- Has anyone ruled out<i> H. pylori?</i>

273
00:12:43,813 --> 00:12:45,775
- This is a GI problem.
- This is neuropathic.

274
00:12:45,799 --> 00:12:47,410
- It's psychological.
- Nerve conditions.

275
00:12:47,434 --> 00:12:49,434
- Battery of tests.
- After I get nerve conditions.

276
00:12:51,138 --> 00:12:52,537
What's going on? I didn't ask

277
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:53,816
for any consults
on this patient.

278
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,623
Our attending did.

279
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:57,436
We can't rule out
biliary dyskinesia, either,

280
00:12:57,460 --> 00:12:59,627
until we do a CCK-HIDA scan.

281
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:01,774
- Gen surg isn't even here.
- Look who finally showed up.

282
00:13:01,798 --> 00:13:03,459
Nigel, I'm sorry.
Give me one second.

283
00:13:03,483 --> 00:13:04,816
Can I talk to you, Dr. Wilmot?

284
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:13,641
You're not usually on
the floor post rounds.

285
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,221
I don't have to account
for my whereabouts.

286
00:13:15,245 --> 00:13:16,755
I'm your attending.
You report to me,

287
00:13:16,779 --> 00:13:18,379
not the other way around.

288
00:13:18,465 --> 00:13:20,443
- You requested consults on my patient.
- Yeah.

289
00:13:20,467 --> 00:13:22,901
- Why?
- Yeah, I think the question is why didn't you?

290
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:26,020
He's already had every test
you're coming up with in there.

291
00:13:26,088 --> 00:13:28,656
Not at Chastain.
We run our own tests.

292
00:13:28,725 --> 00:13:30,558
Nigel is sick of doctors.

293
00:13:30,627 --> 00:13:32,622
He's been poked
and prodded for years.

294
00:13:32,646 --> 00:13:33,911
I'm just giving him a breather

295
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:35,725
while all his medical records
are sent from New York.

296
00:13:35,749 --> 00:13:37,827
And meanwhile, he sits
around in constant pain?

297
00:13:37,851 --> 00:13:40,918
Pain that can be exacerbated
by unnecessary procedures.

298
00:13:40,987 --> 00:13:43,620
Oh, see, this has always
been your problem, Hawkins.

299
00:13:43,689 --> 00:13:45,618
You think your
way is the only way.

300
00:13:45,642 --> 00:13:48,376
Look, I... I just want to go
over his previous test results

301
00:13:48,444 --> 00:13:50,306
before subjecting
him to new ones.

302
00:13:50,330 --> 00:13:51,740
Yeah, well, look, it's
not your call anymore

303
00:13:51,764 --> 00:13:52,596
because he's no
longer your patient.

304
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:53,764
He's mine now.

305
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,649
Thank you.

306
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:05,576
How you feeling?

307
00:14:05,629 --> 00:14:07,812
I'm just gonna check
your pupils, okay?

308
00:14:07,881 --> 00:14:10,798
Doc, are these
restraints necessary?

309
00:14:10,884 --> 00:14:12,649
I'm cool now. For real.

310
00:14:12,718 --> 00:14:14,830
I'm actually a nurse
practitioner, not a doctor.

311
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:17,421
And yes, they are. They're
for your own protection.

312
00:14:17,474 --> 00:14:20,140
So, I guess the cops
are coming, huh?

313
00:14:20,209 --> 00:14:21,987
Well, looks like
it's your lucky day.

314
00:14:22,011 --> 00:14:24,712
Dr. Okafor decided
not to press charges.

315
00:14:25,732 --> 00:14:27,865
I haven't exactly had

316
00:14:27,934 --> 00:14:30,835
a lot of lucky days lately.

317
00:14:30,904 --> 00:14:32,753
I called your parents.

318
00:14:32,822 --> 00:14:33,987
Why?

319
00:14:34,056 --> 00:14:35,668
They don't want
nothing to do with me.

320
00:14:35,692 --> 00:14:37,036
Because someone has
to come and get you.

321
00:14:37,060 --> 00:14:38,554
If y'all for real not
calling the cops,

322
00:14:38,578 --> 00:14:39,888
- then just release me.
- On your own?

323
00:14:39,912 --> 00:14:41,490
So you can go back
out onto the street

324
00:14:41,514 --> 00:14:42,675
and score again?
I don't think so.

325
00:14:42,699 --> 00:14:44,009
Plus, you have
lorazepam in your system.

326
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:46,217
- You could OD.
- No. Seriously...

327
00:14:46,286 --> 00:14:48,786
after everything
that happened today,

328
00:14:48,838 --> 00:14:49,770
I'm done with that mess.

329
00:14:49,839 --> 00:14:51,555
I'm-a get clean.

330
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:53,657
I've heard that before.

331
00:14:53,727 --> 00:14:56,076
Why you care so much
about me anyway?

332
00:14:56,145 --> 00:14:59,647
Is there anyone else who
can come pick you up?

333
00:14:59,715 --> 00:15:00,982
Nah.

334
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:02,850
I got no one.

335
00:15:05,772 --> 00:15:08,739
So what happens to me now?

336
00:15:19,219 --> 00:15:21,219
What are you doing?

337
00:15:22,204 --> 00:15:23,888
Taking Atiba home.

338
00:15:23,956 --> 00:15:25,306
I asked you to call his parents,

339
00:15:25,375 --> 00:15:26,874
not turn into his personal taxi.

340
00:15:26,942 --> 00:15:28,387
Well, his parents
aren't coming to get him,

341
00:15:28,411 --> 00:15:29,972
so I'm going to
take him to them.

342
00:15:29,996 --> 00:15:32,646
Have you lost your mind?

343
00:15:32,716 --> 00:15:33,959
Y'all know I'm standing
right here, right?

344
00:15:33,983 --> 00:15:35,682
Be quiet. You tried to mug me.

345
00:15:35,769 --> 00:15:36,896
You don't get to say anything.

346
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:38,735
I'm sorry. This-this morning

347
00:15:38,805 --> 00:15:39,865
I wasn't thinking st...

348
00:15:39,889 --> 00:15:41,355
I'm-a stop talking now.

349
00:15:41,441 --> 00:15:42,618
- Mm-hmm.
- Look, my shift is over.

350
00:15:42,642 --> 00:15:43,508
I'm giving him a ride.

351
00:15:43,576 --> 00:15:44,616
It's not a big deal.

352
00:15:44,660 --> 00:15:47,545
Damn<i> oyibo</i> savior complex.

353
00:15:49,749 --> 00:15:52,166
Someone has to protect
you from yourself...

354
00:15:52,234 --> 00:15:53,467
and him.

355
00:15:53,536 --> 00:15:54,902
Plus, he's my patient.

356
00:15:54,988 --> 00:15:56,933
So, you're stuck
with both of us now.

357
00:15:56,957 --> 00:15:58,923
That's fine by me.

358
00:15:58,991 --> 00:16:00,841
Get your ass

359
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:01,926
in the back seat.

360
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,073
It's quite a view, isn't it?

361
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:18,943
Never fails to
impress. You rang?

362
00:16:19,012 --> 00:16:21,913
Yeah, about an hour ago.

363
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,514
I was in surgery.

364
00:16:23,566 --> 00:16:26,700
Ah, Mr. Levine's
parathyroidectomy. How was that?

365
00:16:26,770 --> 00:16:28,447
A success. I
think you'll find him

366
00:16:28,471 --> 00:16:30,071
very indebted to Chastain.

367
00:16:30,139 --> 00:16:32,723
I had the scheduling
nurse clear your afternoon.

368
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:36,093
I ran into Dr. Edmund
Carver from St. Grace

369
00:16:36,162 --> 00:16:38,178
last night at the opera.

370
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:39,714
He's in town briefly,

371
00:16:39,783 --> 00:16:41,326
and I invited him
here for coffee today.

372
00:16:41,350 --> 00:16:44,786
And you'd like me
to attend that coffee.

373
00:16:44,854 --> 00:16:46,331
Every reputable
hospital in the country

374
00:16:46,355 --> 00:16:47,955
is trying to recruit Carver

375
00:16:48,024 --> 00:16:50,290
after his surgery on the
former attorney general.

376
00:16:50,359 --> 00:16:52,960
I want Carver at Chastain.

377
00:16:53,029 --> 00:16:54,795
I hear he's overrated.

378
00:16:54,864 --> 00:16:56,014
Maybe.

379
00:16:56,082 --> 00:16:57,932
But with your guidance,

380
00:16:58,001 --> 00:17:01,735
he would be an incredible
asset to your team.

381
00:17:01,805 --> 00:17:03,104
You just talk to him.

382
00:17:03,173 --> 00:17:05,939
Show him around,
give him the full Bell.

383
00:17:06,008 --> 00:17:07,891
Close that deal for me.

384
00:17:08,994 --> 00:17:11,595
Consider it closed.

385
00:17:11,648 --> 00:17:13,864
Thank you.

386
00:17:22,692 --> 00:17:24,553
So, who are we mad at today?

387
00:17:24,577 --> 00:17:25,617
Other than that pen.

388
00:17:25,644 --> 00:17:26,977
How much time do you have?

389
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,580
Anything I can help with?

390
00:17:29,632 --> 00:17:31,965
I convinced a patient
with unknown chronic pain

391
00:17:32,034 --> 00:17:34,012
to stay and let me try
and help him, but then...

392
00:17:34,036 --> 00:17:35,865
Word gets out, and
the vultures descend.

393
00:17:35,889 --> 00:17:38,200
Yep. I'll give you two guesses.
Who was the leader of the pack?

394
00:17:38,224 --> 00:17:40,958
Sampson in Neuro. He
can never resist a call

395
00:17:41,027 --> 00:17:43,611
for a mystery diagnosis.
Allows him to bill

396
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:45,780
- a ton for testing.
- Oh, he was there.

397
00:17:45,848 --> 00:17:47,492
But today's prize
goes to Wilmot.

398
00:17:47,516 --> 00:17:48,949
Took over the case.

399
00:17:49,018 --> 00:17:50,963
Wants to ensure if we
figure out the diagnosis,

400
00:17:50,987 --> 00:17:52,987
he gets the win.

401
00:17:53,055 --> 00:17:55,723
You sure it's just Wilmot
that's bothering you?

402
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:57,875
Hey. You're a hard man to find.

403
00:17:57,944 --> 00:18:00,828
- Well, you found me.
- Wilmot asked me to consult

404
00:18:00,897 --> 00:18:03,314
on a possible lap
chole for Nigel Meahan.

405
00:18:03,382 --> 00:18:06,000
You and Wilmot want
to unnecessarily remove

406
00:18:06,068 --> 00:18:07,746
a man's gallbladder
without even knowing

407
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:09,014
if that's the
source of his pain?

408
00:18:09,038 --> 00:18:10,888
Well, for the record,

409
00:18:10,957 --> 00:18:13,457
I told him it was premature
to consider surgery.

410
00:18:18,598 --> 00:18:20,898
So, has he been biting
everyone's head off today,

411
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:23,316
- or just mine?
- Depends.

412
00:18:23,385 --> 00:18:25,653
What'd you do?

413
00:18:25,721 --> 00:18:28,021
<i>You know, you really didn't</i>

414
00:18:28,108 --> 00:18:30,152
have to escort me to my
conditioning personally.

415
00:18:30,176 --> 00:18:33,060
Well, don't tell me
you're sick of me already.

416
00:18:33,146 --> 00:18:35,763
You know, once my
immune system is stripped,

417
00:18:35,832 --> 00:18:39,717
just how isolated am
I gonna have to be?

418
00:18:39,786 --> 00:18:42,319
Are we talking no contact? Or...

419
00:18:42,388 --> 00:18:44,955
- It's for your safety, Lily.
- No, I know.

420
00:18:45,975 --> 00:18:48,509
That's stupid, right?

421
00:18:48,578 --> 00:18:51,512
You'd think I'd be used
to being alone by now.

422
00:18:57,053 --> 00:18:59,754
I thought we were
headed to conditioning.

423
00:18:59,822 --> 00:19:01,822
We have time.

424
00:19:03,192 --> 00:19:06,110
Talk to me, Lily.

425
00:19:06,179 --> 00:19:08,962
What's really going on?

426
00:19:10,984 --> 00:19:13,584
Well, this is the right
thing for me, right?

427
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:15,970
The bone marrow transplant?

428
00:19:17,006 --> 00:19:18,873
I've been doing some reading,

429
00:19:18,942 --> 00:19:20,892
and once we start,

430
00:19:20,944 --> 00:19:23,210
there's no turning back.

431
00:19:25,214 --> 00:19:28,082
You're scared. I get it.

432
00:19:28,151 --> 00:19:30,251
But that's-that's
totally normal.

433
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:32,102
I know.

434
00:19:32,172 --> 00:19:35,839
I have a 62% survival
rate in my first year.

435
00:19:37,109 --> 00:19:40,411
That's a 38% chance of dying.

436
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:43,396
But no doctor has ever
just come out and said that.

437
00:19:43,465 --> 00:19:45,265
Besides, there's...

438
00:19:45,334 --> 00:19:47,374
there's other
complications. I mean...

439
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:49,937
it could damage
my organs. Infertility.

440
00:19:50,006 --> 00:19:53,140
I want to have
kids one day, and...

441
00:19:53,226 --> 00:19:55,526
God.

442
00:19:55,595 --> 00:19:58,795
Listen to me.

443
00:19:58,865 --> 00:20:00,681
Self-pity is so attractive.

444
00:20:03,169 --> 00:20:05,302
You know what? Ignore me.

445
00:20:05,371 --> 00:20:07,921
Bone marrow
transplants save lives.

446
00:20:07,991 --> 00:20:10,324
I need a transplant, so
I'm going to get a transplant.

447
00:20:10,393 --> 00:20:12,827
End of story.

448
00:20:19,802 --> 00:20:21,735
I understand, but...

449
00:20:21,804 --> 00:20:24,355
I don't care what my
husband told y'all on the phone.

450
00:20:24,424 --> 00:20:26,807
Atiba is not welcome
back in our lives.

451
00:20:26,893 --> 00:20:28,904
It's not safe for him to
be out on the streets.

452
00:20:28,928 --> 00:20:30,127
He could OD at any time.

453
00:20:30,196 --> 00:20:32,074
Monique, if he's
trying to get clean...

454
00:20:32,098 --> 00:20:32,980
Do I look like a fool?

455
00:20:33,049 --> 00:20:35,466
I'm done helping him.

456
00:20:35,535 --> 00:20:36,984
That is not the boy I raised.

457
00:20:37,053 --> 00:20:39,987
I know how difficult it is

458
00:20:40,073 --> 00:20:41,283
to watch someone you
love suffer through a disease

459
00:20:41,307 --> 00:20:42,835
- like this...
- Really, missy?

460
00:20:42,859 --> 00:20:44,791
Do you have kids?

461
00:20:44,861 --> 00:20:46,922
Do you know what
it's like to come to work

462
00:20:46,946 --> 00:20:48,979
and find your store robbed

463
00:20:49,032 --> 00:20:50,809
and then realize
that your boy did it

464
00:20:50,833 --> 00:20:52,015
for drug money?

465
00:20:52,085 --> 00:20:54,184
Or to come home and find

466
00:20:54,254 --> 00:20:56,098
your baby alone
in a soiled diaper,

467
00:20:56,122 --> 00:20:57,821
crying for hours

468
00:20:57,890 --> 00:20:59,935
because his brother's
passed out in the bathroom?

469
00:20:59,959 --> 00:21:01,937
You're trying to protect
what's left of your family.

470
00:21:01,961 --> 00:21:03,594
I do understand that.

471
00:21:03,663 --> 00:21:05,524
But I also know you
still love your son.

472
00:21:05,548 --> 00:21:07,681
What if he really is

473
00:21:07,767 --> 00:21:09,783
willing to get help?

474
00:21:09,852 --> 00:21:12,018
He can beat this.

475
00:21:12,087 --> 00:21:14,838
Monique.

476
00:21:14,891 --> 00:21:16,390
Come on. Just hear him out.

477
00:21:16,458 --> 00:21:18,225
Come on.

478
00:21:19,228 --> 00:21:22,012
I'm for real this time, Mom.

479
00:21:23,082 --> 00:21:25,116
Please.

480
00:21:28,121 --> 00:21:30,037
I'll go in a program.

481
00:21:30,105 --> 00:21:32,172
I swear.

482
00:21:32,241 --> 00:21:35,091
I'll do whatever you say.

483
00:21:39,248 --> 00:21:41,165
Ma!

484
00:21:46,706 --> 00:21:48,939
That boy won't be
able to stay clean.

485
00:21:49,007 --> 00:21:50,390
He hasn't hit rock bottom yet.

486
00:21:50,459 --> 00:21:52,154
Yeah, well, you
can't give up hope,

487
00:21:52,178 --> 00:21:53,655
'cause while you're
waiting for rock bottom,

488
00:21:53,679 --> 00:21:55,279
you could end up dead.

489
00:21:55,348 --> 00:21:56,913
So, who is it?

490
00:21:56,982 --> 00:21:59,883
The way you're talking
only comes from experience.

491
00:21:59,952 --> 00:22:01,552
So who is it?

492
00:22:01,621 --> 00:22:03,687
My sister.

493
00:22:08,911 --> 00:22:11,045
Hey. I need a full
panel on Lily Kendall.

494
00:22:11,114 --> 00:22:14,064
Her most recent
labs are in her file.

495
00:22:14,117 --> 00:22:17,451
Thank you, but I'd still like
to have a full panel done.

496
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,281
You've worked here long
enough that I shouldn't have

497
00:22:19,305 --> 00:22:20,571
to explain this to you.

